# DevOps K8s troubleshooting agent — optional real-service config.
#
# The smoke path and the tests run with the STANDARD LIBRARY ONLY: a mock
# cluster, a mock Slack, and a deterministic mock model. Nothing below is needed
# to run `python smoke.py` or `python -m pytest tests/`. Set these only when you
# deliberately opt in to real services on infrastructure you own.

# --- Real model (opt-in) ----------------------------------------------------
# Reason over findings with a frontier model instead of the deterministic mock.
# USE_REAL_LLM=1
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...

# --- Real Kubernetes (opt-in) -----------------------------------------------
# Point the specialists at a real cluster via a READ-ONLY credential. Use the
# AKS RBAC Reader role (read-only namespace access; cannot view Secrets, cannot
# mutate). Never hand this agent a Writer/Admin role — diagnosis is read-only.
# KUBECONFIG=/path/to/readonly-kubeconfig
# K8S_NAMESPACE=storefront

# --- Real Slack (opt-in) ----------------------------------------------------
# Swap MockSlack for a real approval card. The bot posts the proposal and waits
# for a button click; silence is never a yes.
# SLACK_BOT_TOKEN=xoxb-...
# SLACK_APPROVAL_CHANNEL=C0123456789
